begin_memory_text: We talked about country music and the areas in which we live.
middle_memory_text: We talked about wildlife, politics, Covid and a my life and his life.
end_memory_text: We talked about various things from money to political ads to me being a single mom to him being raised by a single mom.
rest_of_day_open: I will go to work and spend most of the week sitting there being bored.  I will take Friday off and have a long weekend where I will likely not do too much either.  I think that the week will be very long and boring and I will long for it to be over.
critical_positive: I felt that he listened to me and tried not to talk over me.  If he accidentally interrupted me, then he would quickly apologize.  He told me that he was nervous but he was still able to talk easily and openly with me.  He told me things that he felt comfortable talking about with me.
critical_negative: There were a few times when there was a bit of a pause where we really didn't know what to talk about.  It was very noticeable that he was quite nervous.  I think it was more awkward for him that it was for me but I could tell that his nervousness was getting to him.

begin_memory_text: Att and intermittent internet. Buck Owen's and country music.

end_memory_text: The election. Admiration for single mothers. The att and fiber and dsl problem. Being grateful for what you have.
rest_of_day_open: It will be rather bland and blase. I will attempt to buy another smartphone if and only if there is another price reduction for prime week. I will listen to joe biden answer questions. I will cook for family. I will go to Fort Tejon and walk around. I will otherwise occupy my time with more studies
critical_positive: Our mutual knowledge, however little, of Buck Owen's and the older country stars that passed away. Our disdain for what is happening in the country now and the sheer number of crises which worries us. Our mutual sense of humor and belief in being grateful. Our patience with the technology we were using.
critical_negative: My shyness. Bad connection: we lost each others picture for awhile. Our getting stuck and not knowing what topic to discuss or how to continue. My general ineptitude with speech and anxiety. She had a tendency to laugh when I felt ashamed to try to ease what I was feeling, but I sensed some judgement as I revealed more about myself and being I'll and not driving.
